Asking them to "duel" is exactly what they want.  By fighting a friend's (db or higher) pet, you can gain skill-ups.  Though, I think you actually need to be in an arena and not in a /duel.  Better in an arena, because once you /duel someone, they can't cast buffs on you until you zone out or die.  In an arena, they can.

Best bet is to go to Allakhazam's and find the fastest 2hs weapon you can get.  For short races, it's the Rantho Rapier from Rivervale (easy quest).  For large or medium races, I'm not sure.

Best is a Shaman pet.  He can haste you and heal you.  His pet isn't uber, either.  Just make sure you both watch your HP and the pet's HP.  Silly to make the shaman recast his pet if you kill it...and a shame if you die.

